1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:34,780
First

Floor



Inside

the Castle

3
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:41,460
A Kunoichi's Oath

4
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:38,290
It's Straw Hat and Jinbe!

5
00:01:38,290 --> 00:01:40,370
They're crazy strong!

6
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:41,960
Watch out!

7
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:45,000
Why didn't they mention "Black Leg"?!

8
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,840
Just run!

9
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,170
I know!

10
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:49,420
I wanna kick Kaido's ass!

11
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:50,380
Stop!

12
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:51,510
You won't get through!

13
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,930
You weaklings are pathetic!

14
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:04,520
Forgive us... Master Hamlet,
Master Fourtricks...

15
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:06,440
We couldn't stop them!

16
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,780
"Ordinary"?

17
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:11,860
A fitting word for rabble such as yourself!

18
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:13,240
"Expectations"?

19
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:16,370
Those are for us to surpass!

20
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,830
Headliner Hamlet

Beast Pirates

Giraffe Smile Fruit

21
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:23,250
Quiet yourself, Hamlet.

22
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:25,500
The truly powerful remain silent.

23
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,210
– Master Hamlet!
– Master Fourtricks!

24
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,210
Headliner Fourtricks

Beast Pirates

Chicken Smile Fruit

25
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:30,170
That looks wrong!

26
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,430
– Master Hamlet!
– Master Fourtricks!

27
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:41,310
Wait for me, Kaido!

28
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:14,470
Kiku!

29
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:29,150
Get away from the rooftop!

30
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,360
Yes, sir!

31
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:48,420
Then... if you would...

32
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:23,030
Can you stand, Kikunojo?

33
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,540
Of course.

34
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:38,130
That's more like it...

35
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:41,550
Your determination never runs dry.

36
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:43,640
I love...

37
00:04:44,180 --> 00:04:47,100
the way of the samurai.

38
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,440
Roger...

39
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:52,100
Whitebeard...

40
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,270
Now they did it right!

41
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:07,870
Call me old-fashioned, but...

42
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:12,920
death completes a man.

43
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,800
Do you not agree?

44
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,380
Let's finish this!

45
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:25,390
Stow your arrogance, Kaido!

46
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:30,480
There is no honor in falling by your hand!

47
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,140
None!

48
00:05:37,650 --> 00:05:41,150
How are you enjoying my plague rounds?!

49
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:45,530
No way...

50
00:05:45,530 --> 00:05:47,240
It's cold...

51
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:50,710
Help me, please...!

52
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,960
Hold on, stop!

53
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,050
We're on the same side!

54
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:02,840
Your Awesomeness,
why did you shoot us, too?!

55
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:10,680
It's cold! It's cold! I'm becoming an ogre...

56
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:13,390
Help me, please!

57
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:18,900
All you guys do is laugh anyway!

58
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,900
Make yourselves useful for once, Pleasures!

59
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:25,620
Help me...

60
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:32,290
There was still some humanity left in him!

61
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:36,040
Either way, he was going to become
an ogre soon. The outcome is the same.

62
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,380
I suppose that's true.

63
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:41,710
More importantly, where did
the commander go?

64
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:42,760
No idea!

65
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:45,180
We need to focus on survival!

66
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,850
No mercy even for their allies?!

67
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:51,140
Omasa!

68
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:55,100
Dammit...!

69
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:58,610
I'm sorry, Boss Hyogoro...

70
00:06:59,570 --> 00:07:03,490
I'll die before I hurt any of you!

71
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:05,950
Don't jump the gun, you fool!

72
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,040
I don't want to be an ogre!

73
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,500
There must be a cure!

74
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:19,500
I'll cut you down myself
if there's no other option!

75
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,630
There's no need to end it yourself!

76
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:23,590
If this goes on...

77
00:07:23,590 --> 00:07:26,470
Is there anything you can do, Chopper?!

78
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:32,970
Realistically, it's not possible to develop a cure
in the middle of battle, let alone distribute it.

79
00:07:32,970 --> 00:07:33,980
Then...

80
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:40,060
But unlike back in Udon, we have
the guy who made the virus right here!

81
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:46,280
Whoever created the virus would have also created
an antibody at the same time and kept it around.

82
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:51,450
If I get that antibody,
I can synthesize a ton of medicine!

83
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:54,160
Of all the people to have it, it's a Superstar!

84
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,410
Getting it will be next to impossible!

85
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:19,730
Forget the aggression, I'm more concerned about
what's going to happen if we leave them like this!

86
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:24,780
Not only are their muscles and ferocity growing,
their skin is cooling unusually fast!

87
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,910
Their bodies won't be able to handle it!

88
00:08:31,620 --> 00:08:34,080
How do I keep these guys
from getting back up?

89
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,620
Are they zombies?!

90
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:42,170
So you're saying that if we
leave them like this...

91
00:08:42,170 --> 00:08:44,380
They'll die!

92
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:50,970
Once you get infected, you only
have an hour left at the most!

93
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:53,220
What?!

94
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:57,600
Was the person who turned
into an ice ogre your best friend?

95
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,890
Your boss?

96
00:08:58,890 --> 00:09:00,310
Your subordinate?

97
00:09:00,310 --> 00:09:03,110
I'm sure they've never felt as full of energy
as they do right this very second!

98
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:05,820
I'm sure they've never felt as full of energy
as they do right this very second!

99
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:10,070
Make sure you give 'em one last big hug!

100
00:09:11,070 --> 00:09:12,910
But you might catch the bug!

101
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:20,290
Dammit, Queen!

102
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:23,750
How could he make another
messed-up weapon like this?!

103
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:27,380
I gotta get the hell off this floor!

104
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:33,140
Hey! Open the door!

105
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:37,180
Hey! Brother Apoo!

106
00:09:42,730 --> 00:09:44,400
What's this?

107
00:09:44,810 --> 00:09:48,530
That right there is the only antibody
in the whole world!

108
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:51,280
Oh, for Ice Ogre?

109
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:55,280
If you lose it, your punishment will be
one hell of a brutal death...

110
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,490
Death...?

111
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:58,120
– An antibody...
– An antibody...

112
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,500
...against Ice Ogre?

113
00:10:03,330 --> 00:10:05,580
What? What?!

114
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:06,790
Whaaat?!

115
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:10,260
Queen presents!

116
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:14,180
Game... Time!

117
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:20,180
Zoomin', zoomin', zoomin', zoomin'

118
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:22,100
Zoomin', zoomin', zoomin', zoomin'

119
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,730
Zoomin', zoomin', zoomin', zoomin'

120
00:10:23,730 --> 00:10:25,860
Zoomin', zoomin', zoomin', zoomin'

121
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:29,440
Let's party hardy buddy,
'cause it's time to play!

122
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:33,860
A game just ain't a game
if it ain't got any stakes!

123
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:40,330
Murder! Betrayal! There ain't no rules today!

124
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:43,290
'Cause in an hour, sucka, you are gonna...

125
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:44,870
die!

126
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:47,840
It's a plague!

127
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,340
That bastard!

128
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:51,800
Are people's lives worth nothing to him?!

129
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,590
Ice ogre...

130
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:58,050
tag!

131
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:59,720
Whoa!

132
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,350
Whoa, whoa!

133
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:04,810
Zoro! Get that antibody from him!

134
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:05,940
Got it!

135
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:07,730
Don't let them have it!

136
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:09,190
Our men are gonna die!

137
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:11,730
Don't let the samurai recover!

138
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,360
Hold on a second, Queen!

139
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:19,580
You crazy-ass bastard!

140
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:22,290
Start!

141
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:26,370
Steal it from each other!

142
00:11:26,370 --> 00:11:27,750
Murder for it!

143
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:33,010
As long as you don't
get caught, you win, Apoo!

144
00:11:33,010 --> 00:11:34,720
Everyone else will die!

145
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,390
Dammit!

146
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:51,320
Right-Brain Tower

Inside the Dome

147
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:56,450
You really think you can outrun us
while carrying them?

148
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:05,450
Anyway, as long as we kill the brat,
our mission is complete.

149
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:08,790
Don't worry.

150
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:10,750
I'll protect you.

151
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:12,250
Why do you...

152
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:15,210
fight for the Kozuki?

153
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:21,220
I do not know who you are,
but if you are on our side...

154
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,890
please save Lord Momonosuke!

155
00:12:26,890 --> 00:12:29,940
I'm saving you, too, Shinobu!

156
00:12:29,940 --> 00:12:30,650
What?

157
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,900
Twenty years ago...

158
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:38,110
I witnessed Kozuki Oden's execution firsthand!

159
00:12:57,340 --> 00:13:03,010
Don't you understand that you
owe your peaceful lives to him?!

160
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:12,810
Lord Oden has always been
this country's guardian!

161
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:15,610
Now, can you still call him a fool?!

162
00:13:15,610 --> 00:13:18,190
Tell me!

163
00:13:19,570 --> 00:13:22,240
Your speech brought me to tears!

164
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:30,750
Not only that...

165
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:33,630
Kozuki Oden's way of life
brought me to tears, too!

166
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:56,150
Momonosuke.

167
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,320
On that terrible day,

168
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,320
in order to save you...

169
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,370
I ran to Kuri.

170
00:14:06,370 --> 00:14:10,000
What?! Then how... are you alive?

171
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,750
But...

172
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:13,750
I'm sorry...

173
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:20,210
All I could do was watch as Kaido
dangled you over the edge!

174
00:14:33,850 --> 00:14:34,900
Back then,

175
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:38,110
I wasn't strong enough!

176
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:44,860
Huh?

177
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:02,880
Wh-Who are you?

178
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:07,180
You identified yourself as my father...

179
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:08,760
Kozuki Oden!

180
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,970
My other name is...

181
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,850
Yamato!

182
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,490
And I...

183
00:15:24,490 --> 00:15:27,110
would die for you!

184
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:33,500
Marco!

185
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:39,170
I may not understand
my role in this war just yet...

186
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:43,670
but I know better than the Straw Hats
how dangerous you are!

187
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:51,680
Hey! Prometheus!

188
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:53,520
Yes, Mama!

189
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:55,390
Ready?!

190
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:58,600
Heavenly Feuer!

191
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:07,320
There's no room for you
on the ships bound for the new era!

192
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:12,660
Keep your mouth shut!

193
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,540
Why are his flames overpowering mine?!

194
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:22,710
Prometheus!

195
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:32,350
Phoenix flames...

196
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:34,310
are of legendary stock!

197
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:37,060
Why, you little...

198
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:38,560
How dare you?!

199
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,360
You let your guard down, huh?

200
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:47,110
Good luck getting away now!

201
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:50,450
Take the shot, Perospero!

202
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:53,080
Okay, Mama!

203
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,410
Lick.

204
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,920
Sorry, Marco...

205
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:07,630
I'll be letting Mama help me out!

206
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:10,380
Damn...

207
00:17:10,380 --> 00:17:14,260
There were so many other times where
I relished the thought of killing you.

208
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:16,100
How ironic.

209
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:24,230
Goodbye...

210
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,910
– Moon...
– Moon...

211
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:34,370
– Raid!
– Raid!

212
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:47,500
I-It's you again! From before!

213
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,170
You keep getting in my way!

214
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,140
Is this the man who killed Pedro?!

215
00:17:56,470 --> 00:17:57,850
Yes!

216
00:17:57,850 --> 00:17:59,520
If it weren't for him...

217
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:03,270
That idiot Pedro blew himself up!

218
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:06,150
He caused trouble for me!

219
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:11,900
I'm certain that Pedro's death
is what led us to this battle.

220
00:18:15,740 --> 00:18:19,160
You-gara must press on!

221
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:22,660
Oh, this is just perfect!

222
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:27,670
Don't bring something as petty as revenge...

223
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:32,550
to the edge of a battlefield!

224
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:36,180
Well, do whatever you want!

225
00:18:44,650 --> 00:18:45,730
Who are you two?!

226
00:18:46,150 --> 00:18:47,520
Carrot.

227
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:48,730
Wanda.

228
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:50,860
And you're Marco.

229
00:18:51,490 --> 00:18:54,110
A friend of Master Nekomamushi's, right?

230
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:56,370
I guess you could say that...

231
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:58,580
Marco!

232
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:02,250
If you wanna kill me,
it'll have to be some other time!

233
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:05,210
I don't wanna waste
any souls on you right now!

234
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,380
Go, Marco!

235
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:10,300
Leave him to us!

236
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,840
Alright, I'm counting on you!

237
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:24,560
What is that?

238
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:31,110
Hold it!

239
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:32,440
Give me that!

240
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:37,200
Stop chasing me!

241
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:47,000
Wait! Wait!

242
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:47,750
Wait!

243
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,250
Two against one isn't fair!

244
00:19:54,510 --> 00:19:55,340
Man...!

245
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:00,850
I'd rather be helping out Kin'emon!

246
00:20:00,850 --> 00:20:04,430
Fighting you is a huge waste of time!

247
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:07,940
And I've always hated you!

248
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,980
The feeling's mutual, jackass!

249
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,740
Drake... that asshole...

250
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:22,120
Can't believe he did a complete 180
after getting caught!

251
00:20:22,620 --> 00:20:24,080
I see...

252
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,750
So that's Roronoa Zoro.

253
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:33,380
Better take out Straw Hat's
number two and three as soon as possible.

254
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,760
Speaking of which...

255
00:20:35,130 --> 00:20:38,470
I had no idea Judge's son was on their crew.

256
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:44,260
Vinsmoke Judge's son, Sanji!

257
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:49,140
I thought I would turn into an ogre...

258
00:20:49,140 --> 00:20:50,900
But look at me!

259
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:53,020
I'm just fine!

260
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,940
Good!

261
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:58,780
You don't have skin or veins,
and you can't get cold,

262
00:20:58,780 --> 00:21:00,950
so you're practically a corpse!

263
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:04,790
Oh, I see!

264
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:09,040
I suppose my body's always
been like a frigid corpse!

265
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:12,630
That's why I'm not becoming
an ice ogre even though I was infected...

266
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:18,130
It's a little sad!

267
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:19,800
But that means I'm invincible!

268
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:22,260
Wait a minute...

269
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:26,770
Brook's a skeleton, so his temperature
didn't change even when he was infected.

270
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:29,940
That's why the virus didn't multiply.

271
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:34,060
But when a normal person
is infected, their body grows cold.

272
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:37,570
That's what allows the virus
to multiply rapidly...

273
00:21:37,570 --> 00:21:40,900
So if we can find a way
to maintain their temperature...

274
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:42,570
But wait...

275
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,530
how does it freeze them from the inside?

276
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:47,740
Is this...

277
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:50,080
Maybe this virus is...

278
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,580
Chopper!

279
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:53,120
Look at your arm!

280
00:21:56,460 --> 00:21:58,710
What?!

281
00:21:58,710 --> 00:22:00,970
Oh no! I didn't notice!

282
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:07,310
Chopper's gonna die!

283
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,480
Lethal Green Star!

284
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,690
Devil!

285
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:22,450
Ew, ew! So gross!

286
00:22:22,450 --> 00:22:24,240
Alright, got her!

287
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:28,200
Now dissolve her with your
super-strong digestive juices!

288
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:35,630
So slimy... so sticky!

289
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:40,380
Save me, Pay-Pay!

290
00:22:46,050 --> 00:22:48,220
You totally could have freed yourself!

291
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,270
Devil!

292
00:22:55,230 --> 00:22:57,900
Pay-Pay, I love you!

293
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:02,070
Stop! You're all slimy and gross!

294
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,980
I love you so much!

295
00:23:02,070 --> 00:23:04,610
D-D-Damn you!

296
00:23:04,610 --> 00:23:06,530
How about this?!

297
00:23:09,580 --> 00:23:11,200
Bamboo Javelin!

298
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,750
What a boring attack.

299
00:23:26,510 --> 00:23:33,600
I'm not doing this just to have
a good time, you know!

300
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,390
Oh, crap!

301
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:45,570
Ulti-Mortar!

302
00:23:45,570 --> 00:23:46,610
Again?!

303
00:24:00,670 --> 00:24:02,420
Usopp...

304
00:24:03,420 --> 00:24:04,670
Hey, tramp!

305
00:24:06,130 --> 00:24:07,800
Stop!

306
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:11,510
Don't kill me! I surrender! You win!

307
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:17,770
It's pretty damn obvious that you lost!

308
00:24:17,770 --> 00:24:19,690
Now, say it!

309
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:22,480
Say what?

310
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:25,150
I already told you how pissed I am!

311
00:24:25,490 --> 00:24:31,320
After all, your captain said he'll take down
Kaido and become King of the Pirates!

312
00:24:32,780 --> 00:24:34,740
I'm sorry!

313
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:36,370
Luffy...

314
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,870
is a complete idiot!

315
00:24:38,870 --> 00:24:41,710
So please don't headbutt me!

316
00:24:42,290 --> 00:24:43,420
Please!

317
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:44,920
I'll leave the island...

318
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:48,170
I-If you do it again, I'll...

319
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,470
actually die!

320
00:24:50,470 --> 00:24:52,430
Then say it!

321
00:24:52,970 --> 00:24:55,310
Say that your captain...

322
00:24:55,310 --> 00:24:58,600
will never become the King of the Pirates!

323
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,480
Okay...

324
00:25:05,980 --> 00:25:09,200
Luffy will...

325
00:25:15,290 --> 00:25:19,210
Luffy will... Luffy will...

326
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:21,670
never...

327
00:25:22,170 --> 00:25:23,960
That's it, Nami...

328
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,420
It's okay to lie...

329
00:25:26,170 --> 00:25:29,920
If you don't choose your words
carefully, you'll wind up dead!

330
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:31,470
After you've come so far!

331
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:33,930
Lie!

332
00:25:33,930 --> 00:25:35,390
Just lie to her!

333
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:38,310
Luffy will...

334
00:25:40,390 --> 00:25:42,850
never...

335
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:46,610
stop until he's the Pirate King!

336
00:25:47,610 --> 00:25:49,190
I'm sure of it!

337
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:54,490
He will be...

338
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:56,740
Because...

339
00:25:57,580 --> 00:25:58,910
Because... Because...

340
00:25:58,910 --> 00:26:00,830
That's just how it is!

341
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:05,540
Very well, then!

342
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:07,590
Die.

343
00:26:09,710 --> 00:26:11,720
Nami, you moron!

344
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:12,680
Just run!

345
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,640
Onami!

346
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:21,980
Go! Komachiyo!

347
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:27,980
A dog?!

348
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,200
What?!

349
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,200
Is that...

350
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,280
...Otama?!

351
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:39,290
What are you doing here?!
